## Description {#details}

A simple class providing dynamic arbitrary-precision arithmetic.

Internally, it stores an <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/apint">APInt</a>, whose width is doubled whenever an overflow occurs at a certain width. The default constructor sets the initial width to 64. <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/detail/slowdynamicapint">SlowDynamicAPInt</a> is primarily intended to be used as a slow fallback path for the upcoming <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dynamicapint">DynamicAPInt</a> class.

Definition at line 34 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/adt/slowdynamicapint-h">SlowDynamicAPInt.h</a>.
